You should think about the &amp; sign simply replacing it with the current parent selector.

This means:

    .container {
    
        &amp;-white {
            background: white;
        }
    }

becomes

    .container-white {
        background: white;
    }


or:

    .container {
        display: flex;
        &amp;:after {
             content: &#39; &#39;;
             background: black;
        }
    }

becomes:


     .container {
          display: flex;
     }
     .container:after {
          contente: &#39; &#39;;
          background: black;
     }
  

EDIT:
Regarding your example:

    .container {
        display: flex;

        &amp;-footer {
            display: flex;
            margin: 24px 0 8px 8px;

            .CancelButton {
                margin: 0;
            }
        }
     }

The margin on the CancelButton class will be applied only if there will be something like:

